summary: Philip Morris Names Hung as vice president — Pacific/Far East. Mr. Hung was assistant a                Sp ager of the Seven-Up Bottling Co. in Hong Kong. He was also assistant to Philip Mottis, who worked for Philip Morris in London. In 1968, the U.S. government increased cigar taxes by 50%.
